{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Pickard's Pickle","author":"Jim Pickard"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"23db359f-4763-5ce4-bae3-ed251a9f8a8f","excerpt":"I use Neovim on OS X as my code editor.I am quite happy to use it in the terminal, but I find it helpful to have a\nseparate application that I can run in full…","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/5d0d5f73561ef86d9e3e38b3d03577a2/9ad58/cover-image.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 328px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 86.28048780487805%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Neovim running as a standalone app\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/5d0d5f73561ef86d9e3e38b3d03577a2/9ad58/cover-image.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/5d0d5f73561ef86d9e3e38b3d03577a2/cf440/cover-image.png 148w,\n/blog/static/5d0d5f73561ef86d9e3e38b3d03577a2/d2d38/cover-image.png 295w,\n/blog/static/5d0d5f73561ef86d9e3e38b3d03577a2/9ad58/cover-image.png 328w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 328px) 100vw, 328px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>I use Neovim on OS X as my code editor.</p>\n<p>I am quite happy to use it in the terminal, but I find it helpful to have a\nseparate application that I can run in full screen and can switch to\nindependently of iTerm2.</p>\n<p>I tried some of the standalone Neovim applications, but was generally unhappy\nwith them for one reason or another. So I decided to make a standalone version\nthat runs inside iTerm2.</p>\n<p>Running Neovim this way is great because it leverages the power and stability\nof iTerm2. iTerm2 has great support for customization of appearance and\nkeyboard rebinding.</p>\n<p>Here’s how to build a standalone version of Neovim that’s based on iTerm2.</p>\n<p>I am not a developer of Mac applications, so the following is based on a bit of\ntrial and error and fiddling around with XCode. This is the method I’ve used to\nbuild a standalone version of Neovim several times across several versions of\nNeovim and XCode.</p>\n<p>These steps have been tested with XCode 11.2.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Clone iTerm2 master from GitHub <a href=\"https://github.com/gnachman/iTerm2\">https://github.com/gnachman/iTerm2</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Open XCode and choose “Open another project…“. Select the directory where you cloned iTerm2.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/72480/open-another-project.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 59.876543209876544%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Open another project\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/b9e4f/open-another-project.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/cf440/open-another-project.png 148w,\n/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/d2d38/open-another-project.png 295w,\n/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/b9e4f/open-another-project.png 590w,\n/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/f9b6a/open-another-project.png 885w,\n/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/2d849/open-another-project.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/a7a650160577c1bb3fca7fb841995809/72480/open-another-project.png 1620w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Change Bundle ID to (something like) co.uk.cloudship.neovim</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/6a9a9/change-bundle-id.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 41.06548279689234%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Change bundle ID\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/b9e4f/change-bundle-id.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/cf440/change-bundle-id.png 148w,\n/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/d2d38/change-bundle-id.png 295w,\n/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/b9e4f/change-bundle-id.png 590w,\n/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/f9b6a/change-bundle-id.png 885w,\n/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/2d849/change-bundle-id.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/bbefa/change-bundle-id.png 1770w,\n/blog/static/5816d91ad0b02c3f040eccd0d087c272/6a9a9/change-bundle-id.png 1802w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Under Signing &#x26; Capabilities change to “Sign to run locally”</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/ede78/sign-to-run-locally.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 37.04545454545455%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Sign to run locally\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/b9e4f/sign-to-run-locally.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/cf440/sign-to-run-locally.png 148w,\n/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/d2d38/sign-to-run-locally.png 295w,\n/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/b9e4f/sign-to-run-locally.png 590w,\n/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/f9b6a/sign-to-run-locally.png 885w,\n/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/2d849/sign-to-run-locally.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/db98f79e88665237f94f79129a1484ef/ede78/sign-to-run-locally.png 1760w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>In the right-hand pane change Name to Neovim</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/ddb0f33e5c53eca13d33a21e8c194dcf/1fd31/change-name.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 153.46534653465346%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Change name\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/ddb0f33e5c53eca13d33a21e8c194dcf/b9e4f/change-name.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/ddb0f33e5c53eca13d33a21e8c194dcf/cf440/change-name.png 148w,\n/blog/static/ddb0f33e5c53eca13d33a21e8c194dcf/d2d38/change-name.png 295w,\n/blog/static/ddb0f33e5c53eca13d33a21e8c194dcf/b9e4f/change-name.png 590w,\n/blog/static/ddb0f33e5c53eca13d33a21e8c194dcf/1fd31/change-name.png 606w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>A window will appear helping you rename all instances of iTerm2 to Neovim.</p>\n<ol start=\"6\">\n<li>Update the icons.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Find Supporting Files > Images > Media.xcassets (you can use the filter at the\nbottom of the file list window)</p>\n<p>Grab the Neovim icon from here:\n<a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/master/logos/neovim-mark.png\">https://raw.githubusercontent.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/master/logos/neovim-mark.png</a></p>\n<p>I used Iconfly to generate AppIcon.appiconset (select generate without scaling).</p>\n<p>Drag the AppIcon.appiconset folder to Xterm.</p>\n<p>Remove the old icon set and rename the new one to the old name.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/9c10c/update-icons.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 64.95535714285714%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Update icons\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/b9e4f/update-icons.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/cf440/update-icons.png 148w,\n/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/d2d38/update-icons.png 295w,\n/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/b9e4f/update-icons.png 590w,\n/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/f9b6a/update-icons.png 885w,\n/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/2d849/update-icons.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/bbefa/update-icons.png 1770w,\n/blog/static/9e94b4ba8cf516ad14228f63974f6483/9c10c/update-icons.png 1792w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ol start=\"7\">\n<li>I tried building at this point but it failed due to a reference somewhere to iTerm2.pch.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I couldn’t find where it was in the XCode interface so I opened a terminal and\nsearched inside files:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">iTerm2|master⚡ ⇒ ag iTerm2.pch\nNeovim.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj\n14379:                          GCC_PREFIX_HEADER = sources/iTerm2.pch;\n14434:                          GCC_PREFIX_HEADER = sources/iTerm2.pch;\n14499:                          GCC_PREFIX_HEADER = sources/iTerm2.pch;\n14553:                          GCC_PREFIX_HEADER = sources/iTerm2.pch;</code></pre></div>\n<p>I ran a command to change references to iTerm2.pch to Neovim.pch:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">iTerm2|master⚡ ⇒ find . -type f -exec gsed -i &quot;s/iTerm2.pch/Neovim.pch/&quot; {} \\;</code></pre></div>\n<p>At this point XCode will recognize that the files on disk have changed. You\nshould select the “Revert” option, which loads the project from the files in\nthe disk.</p>\n<ol start=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p>Build the application by hitting ⌘-R.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Copy Neovim to applications.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Under Products right click on Neovim.app and select “Show in Finder”.</p>\n<p>Move Neovim.app to applications.</p>\n<ol start=\"10\">\n<li>All done!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You should be able to run Neovim.app now.</p>\n<p>What I did after this was create a separate profile for Neovim in iTerm2 that\nruns the following at startup: <code class=\"language-text\">nvim &amp;&amp; exit</code>. This option is under Profiles >\nGeneral as “send text at start”) in the iTerm2 (and now Neovim) preferences.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/bde20/iterm2-config.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 67.83295711060948%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"iTerm2 config\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/b9e4f/iterm2-config.png\"\n        srcset=\"/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/cf440/iterm2-config.png 148w,\n/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/d2d38/iterm2-config.png 295w,\n/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/b9e4f/iterm2-config.png 590w,\n/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/f9b6a/iterm2-config.png 885w,\n/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/2d849/iterm2-config.png 1180w,\n/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/bbefa/iterm2-config.png 1770w,\n/blog/static/ac8c0e0c8d43ae3f2bc1abe8914defd8/bde20/iterm2-config.png 1772w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Neovim Dot App","date":"November 13, 2019","description":"Creating a standalone Neovim application."}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/neovim-dot-app/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/hello-world/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Hello World"}},"next":null}}